==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yon
<hw>Yon</hw> <pr>(y⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>yon</ets>,
<ets>⟦yogh⟧on</ets>, AS. <ets>geon</ets>; akin to G. <ets>jener</ets>,
OHG. <ets>jen⟦emac⟧r</ets>, Icel. <ets>enn</ets>, <ets>inn</ets>; cf.
Goth. <ets>jains</ets>. ⟦root⟧188. Cf. <er>Beyond</er>, <er>Yond</er>,
<er>Yonder</er>.]</ety> <def>At a distance, but within view;
yonder.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Read thy lot in <qex>yon</qex> celestial sign.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though fast <qex>yon</qex> shower be fleeting.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yon</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Yon
<hw>Yon</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Yonder.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But, first and chiefest, with thee bring⟦br⟧
